LISTSERV Web Interface 2.4.1 2014-11-26T17:56:36Z Rachel Shand 2014-11-26T17:56:19+00:00 2014-11-26T17:56:19+00:00 Moscow in Movement: Power and Opposition in Putin's Russia https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CEELBAS-MASTERS;393dd581.1411 Dear CEELBAS-MASTERS subscribers,<br>We hope the following titles will be of interest to you.<br><br>[Description: Description: Moscow in Movement]<http://www.combinedacademic.co.uk/moscow-in-movement>Moscow in Movement<http://www.combinedacademic.co.uk/moscow-in-movement><br><br>Power and Opposition in Putin's Russia<br>Samuel Greene<br>"Using his own superb empirical work and original theoretical insights, Greene shows that at the center of the postcommunist system in Russia is a fascinating institutional 'disconnect' between the power elite and the society. The latter is not inactive; it is made irrelevant.
